---
import SectionContainer from "../../../components/ui/SectionContainer.astro";
import CTAGroup from "../../../components/ui/CTAGroup.astro";
---

<section class="bg-[#04101f] py-24">

<SectionContainer>

<!-- SECTION HEADER -->

<div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center mb-20">

<h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-semibold text-white">
Why Most Google Ads Appeals Fail — And What Google Actually Looks For
</h2>

<p class="mt-6 text-lg text-gray-300">
Most advertisers submit appeals that are emotional, vague, or incomplete.
Google reviewers expect structured explanations supported by policy-aligned evidence.
</p>

</div>


<!-- EDUCATION GRID -->

<div class="grid gap-8 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 max-w-6xl mx-auto">

<!-- Card 1 -->

<div class="bg-[#081826] border border-white/10 rounded-xl p-8 text-center hover:border-[#6ee7d8]/30 transition">

<img
src="/images/google-ads-suspended-businessman-frustrated-google-email-of-suspension-glow-red-blue-drop-shadow-zoom-on-appeal-man-center.png"
class="mx-auto w-[220px] mb-6"
/>

<h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-3">
Google Suspensions Are Based on Risk Signals
</h3>

<p class="text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
Google does not suspend accounts solely because a rule was broken.
Its systems evaluate whether an advertiser presents a potential risk to users.
</p>

</div>


<!-- Card 2 -->

<div class="bg-[#081826] border border-white/10 rounded-xl p-8 text-center hover:border-[#6ee7d8]/30 transition">

<img
src="/images/policy-aligned-lanuage-google-ads-suspension-review-documents-google-ads-policy.png"
class="mx-auto w-[220px] mb-6"
/>

<h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-3">
Google Reviews More Than Just Ads
</h3>

<p class="text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
Suspensions are rarely triggered by ads alone. Google evaluates websites,
business verification data, account behaviour, and payment signals.
</p>

</div>


<!-- Card 3 -->

<div class="bg-[#081826] border border-white/10 rounded-xl p-8 text-center hover:border-[#6ee7d8]/30 transition">

<img
src="/images/google-ads-evidence-based-supsension-checklist-documentation.png"
class="mx-auto w-[220px] mb-6"
/>

<h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-3">
Appeals Require Supporting Evidence
</h3>

<p class="text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
Successful appeals typically include documentation confirming business legitimacy
and demonstrating policy compliance.
</p>

</div>


<!-- Card 4 -->

<div class="bg-[#081826] border border-white/10 rounded-xl p-8 text-center hover:border-[#6ee7d8]/30 transition">

<img
src="/images/gogole-ads-submission-annoted-documents-subit-an-attachment-girl-whiteboard.png"
class="mx-auto w-[220px] mb-6"
/>

<h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-3">
Structured Appeals Perform Better
</h3>

<p class="text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
Appeals that clearly explain the issue, reference policies, and include supporting
documentation are more likely to receive meaningful review.
</p>

</div>


<!-- Card 5 -->

<div class="bg-[#081826] border border-white/10 rounded-xl p-8 text-center hover:border-[#6ee7d8]/30 transition">

<img
src="/images/agency-approval-for-gogole-ads-suspension-concentrix-google-ads-help-blur.png"
class="mx-auto w-[220px] mb-6"
/>

<h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-3">
Not Every Suspended Account Can Be Recovered
</h3>

<p class="text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
Some suspensions permanently restrict accounts from advertising again.
Eligibility must be assessed before submitting further appeals.
</p>

</div>

</div>


<!-- CTA -->

<div class="mt-20 flex justify-center">
<CTAGroup
href="https://calendly.com/gianluca-adrestore/30min-consultation"
text="Book Suspension Review"
assessmentText="Free 30-Minute Live Account Assessment"
/>
</div>

</SectionContainer>

</section>